What blanket statement?  <br />
<br />
In any given situation common to all humans, the chances of a person having been exposed to the situation before increase with each passing day.  <br />
<br />
Exposure to situations drastically improves your chances of making a correct decision with each experience.<br />
<br />
So the chances of an older person making the correct decision for any circumstance are greater than for a young person.</div>
