Torcer,<br />
<br />
You've made a case that a lot of young liberals (at least, I think you mean &quot;liberal&quot; when you say &quot;idealist&quot;, please correct if I'm wrong) are only liberal because it benefits/doesn't hurt them to be so, and so when these same people become older and richer, then of course they'll become conservative because it benefits them to be so. That is, you've shown a lot of people believe things only because it helps them out personally, and this is true whether you're a young liberal looking for a handout or a rich conservative who wants to lower taxes. <br />
<br />
This has no relevance to whether someone &quot;should&quot; be liberal or conservative, if that's what you were trying to say, which is what I was arguing against.</div>
