	</td>
	
	<td class="alt1" id="td_post_144255">
	
	
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div id="post_message_144255">My point is that if someone grows old and finds themselves turning into a conservative, it's not necessarily because older and wiser people are conservatives, it's because that person likes to believe things that help them out personally, and being a conservative is nice if you are making a good bit of money, which old people tend to do, moreso than young people anyway. And there's nothing wrong with that.<br />
<br />
I was countering Torcer's implication that conservativism is a &quot;wiser&quot; policy because you see a lot of people become conservatives in their older age.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
